videos.description: West Virginia's Will Grier escapes to the left and finds Gary Jennings 32 yards downfield as the Mountaineers jump to a 3-0 lead.
videos.headline: Grier rolls left and throws long ball to set up FG

videos.description: West Virginia quarterback Will Grier throws it up for a streaking David Sills V who jumps over the Baylor defender to score and go up 10-0 at the end of the first quarter.
videos.headline: Sills climbs the ladder for TD catch

videos.description: Baylor's Denzel Mims catches Zach Smith's pass over the middle and outruns the secondary for 45 yards to set up a field goal.
videos.headline: Mims turns on burners to set up FG

videos.description: Mountaineers quarterback Will Grier throws a strike to David Sills V who scores his second touchdown of the game with one second remaining in the first half.
videos.headline: Grier leads West Virginia to score just before half

videos.description: West Virginia's Will Grier finds David Sills V over the middle, and he sprints 53 yards to the end zone for his third score to go up 24-6.
videos.headline: Sills scores third TD on catch and run

videos.description: Baylor's Gavin Holmes catches a pass over the middle and runs 56 yards before being tackled just before the goal line to set up a John Levett touchdown run.
videos.headline: Holmes almost takes it all the way to the house

videos.description: Marcus Simms catches the Will Grier pass over the middle and spins right by the Baylor safety on his way to a score to put West Virginia up 31-13.
videos.headline: Nasty spin moves takes Simms to end zone

videos.description: Mountaineers' receiver Ka'Raun White leaves the Baylor cornerback in his trails as he scores on a 6-yard fade.
videos.headline: White freezes corner on fade for easy TD

videos.description: Baylor's Tresten Ebner finds space along the right sideline and outruns the West Virginia secondary 52 yards to the end zone to cut Baylor's deficit to 18 points.
videos.headline: Ebner keeps Baylor in it with 52-yard TD catch

videos.description: After recovering an onside kick, Baylor's Trestan Ebner scores again on a 40-yard run right down the heart of the West Virginia defense to make it 38-27.
videos.headline: Ebner doing all he can to bring Baylor back

videos.description: Baylor needed just two more points to complete a 25-point comeback, but Baylor quarterback Charlie Brewer is sacked by Xavier Preston to give the Mountaineers the win.
